        <title>Skills employers identify as essential</title>
        <content>&lt;h1 class="Subhead"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #000000;"&gt;Skills employers identify&lt;span style="color: #ffffff;"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;as essential&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span style="line-height: 1.231; font-size: 13px; font-weight: normal;"&gt;The “Are they Really Ready to Work?” study on employer expectations identified two categories of expected skills:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;basic skills; and &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="line-height: 1.231;"&gt;applied skills.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We will explore these two categories in detail on the following screens.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1 class="Subhead"&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;</content>
