      <chapter id="647">
        <pagenum>3</pagenum>
        <subchapter>0</subchapter>
        <title>Basic reading skills</title>
        <content>&lt;h1 class="Subhead"&gt;Basic reading skills&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;Basic Reading&lt;/i&gt; – This is the ability to locate and comprehend critical information from work-related written material, such as technical manuals, and to obtain and understand selected information from the Internet. Many people who are considered to be “functionally illiterate” can actually do this level of reading because they are able to draw information from graphics and illustrations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/115909543.jpg" width="400" height="600" alt="Photo of a male worker with a toolbelt reading instructions." /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content>
