      <chapter id="649">
        <pagenum>5</pagenum>
        <subchapter>0</subchapter>
        <title>Applied skills</title>
        <content>&lt;h1 class="Subhead"&gt;Applied skills&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;Applied skills&lt;/i&gt; refer to those skills that enable workers to use the basic knowledge acquired in school to perform in the workplace. These include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;teamwork/collaboration;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;critical thinking/problem-solving;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;communication;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;professionalism/work ethic;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;information technology application;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;leadership;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;creativity/innovation;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;lifelong learning/self-direction; and&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;ethics/social responsibility.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The skills listed in bold were reported in the “Are they Really Ready to Work?” report as most critical. Let’s take a closer look…&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/MH900431851.JPG" width="239" height="235" alt="Photo of a postal worker’s gloved hands handling a box." /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content>
