      <chapter id="657">
        <pagenum>13</pagenum>
        <subchapter>0</subchapter>
        <title>Applied skills example #1 – teamwork</title>
        <content>&lt;h1 class="Subhead"&gt;Applied skills example #1 – teamwork&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Let’s look at examples of two possible strategies focused on developing teamwork skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Take a moment or so to review the first strategy below. Are there other essential applied skills being developed? How about basic skills? Which ones?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Once you have identified some strategies, click the &lt;b&gt;forward arrow&lt;/b&gt; to compare your answers to ours.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Strategy #1&lt;/b&gt;: Mary divides the class into several small groups and introduces them to a team assignment in which each member is to interview a businessperson to find out how that individual describes what “teamwork” means to him or her. Students are instructed to determine:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;“What does the interviewee see as critical components of teamwork?”&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;“What are examples of teamwork in that person’s workplace?”&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Each group (team) then convenes to share what they learned and to create a unified presentation to the class.&lt;/p&gt;
