        <title>Applied skills example #2 – teamwork</title>
        <content>&lt;h1 class="Subhead"&gt;Applied skills example #2 – teamwork&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Again, please review this strategy. What other essential applied skills are being developed?  How about basic skills?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Once you have identified some strategies, click the &lt;b&gt;forward arrow&lt;/b&gt; to compare your answers to ours.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-left: 30px;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Strategy #2&lt;/b&gt;:  Frank divides his class into small groups and assigns them each a reading selection on the topic of teamwork. After reading the material, each team is to work together to write a paper or prepare an oral presentation on different aspects of teamwork. (Depending on the article, the team might address such issues as goal-setting, assigning tasks according to individual strengths and interests, setting deadlines, following through on tasks, showing commitment to the team, communication, asking for assistance/clarification and creative problem-solving.)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-left: 30px;"&gt;Teams are to demonstrate their use of technology by producing a text or graphic document and/or by preparing a PowerPoint presentation. The team decides in advance how to tackle the assignment. Each team presents its findings to the class and also discusses the dynamics they experienced as a team. Frank then leads the class in a discussion of how all of this relates to an employee’s success in the workplace.&lt;/p&gt;
