        <title>Instructional strategies benefit most adult learners</title>
        <content>&lt;h1 class="Subhead"&gt;Instructional strategies benefit most adult learners&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We covered just two examples of strategies focused on developing skills determined to be essential by employers – both applied and basic. These ideas, as well as your own, are likely to be of great benefit to not only adults with LD, but almost all adult learners you serve.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Let’s move on to examine the career development process, and the instructor’s role in supporting skill development relating to this process.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt; &lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="color: #993300;"&gt;Continue on to Guiding Question #1, Session 2: Career Development&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content>
